accessibility.text: The Creator class defines a factory method for creating product objects, which can be abstract or return a default product type. The factory method helps decouple product creation from the creators core business logic.
Factory Method Responsibility: Decouples product creation logic from concrete product classes.
Factory Method Implementation: Can be declared as abstract to force subclasses to implement their own versions or return a default product type.
Creator Class Role: Primarily responsible for core business logic related to products, not just product creation.
